Executives of Homeland Interactive Technology Ltd ring the bell in Hong Kong on Thursday. The company, which makes online games for mahjong and Chinese poker games, was listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The burgeoning videogame industry in China, which generated $31.2 billion in revenue in 2018, is introducing more elements from Chinese culture. Photo: VCG 
  
